<HEADLINE> ASEAN Science, Technology Exhibition Opens in Hanoi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 12 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of achievements in
science and technology of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) and its dialogue partners opened here Monday,
Vietnam news agency (VNA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is held by Vietnam's national center for
scientific and technological information and the Vietnam
exhibition-fair center as part of ASEAN science and technology
week being held in Hanoi.
</P>
<P>
VNA said that the exhibition, under the theme "science and
technology - dynamic force towards sustainable development in
ASEAN", aims to promote technological transfer between ASEAN
members and ASEAN dialogue partners, boosting regional and
international cooperation in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Research institutes, universities, and businesses from ASEAN
member countries, Australia and India are displaying their
products at 65 stands.
</P>
<P>
The exhibits are outstanding achievements of scientific and
technological activities under ASEAN cooperation programs in food
and foodstuff production, meteorology and geophysics,
micro-electronics and information technology, bio-technology,
materials technology, study of new energy sources, oceanography,
and infrastructures development.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will run until October 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
