<HEADLINE> Congress Leader Attacks Central Government of Plunging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 12 ( Xinhua) -- Congress President Sonia
Gandhi accused Monday the Indian government led by the Bharatiya
Janata Party (BJP) of plunging the country into a grave crisis due
to its wrong policies and internal squabbles and failure to
provide a stable and good government.
</P>
<P>
The BJP-led government had promised to provide a stable and
good government but the outcome has been just the opposite,
creating a dangerous situation, she told her party workers in
Rohtak of the Haryana state, 70 kilometers northwest of here.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, Gandhi said that ever
since the BJP-led government had come to power, divisive forces
had been spreading communal venom and hatred triggering violence
and assault on the country's age-old secular fabric.
</P>
<P>
The main opposition paid a day-long visit to the state of
Haryana today during which she also visited families of about 70
farmers who had committed suicide.
</P>
<P>
She announced that the Congress party would give compensation
to the families and asked congress committees in others states to
go into the farmers's problems and submit reports so that the
party could work out a detailed action plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
