<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore PM on His Country's Competitiveness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong Monday night outlined his country's plan to compete
effectively and capitalize quickly on the opportunities when the
region recovers.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a keynote speech at the official opening dinner of
the Seventh East Asia Economic summit organized by the
Switzerland-based World Economic Forum in partnership with the
Economic Development Board of Singapore, Goh Chok Tong said the
Committee on Singapore's Competitiveness (CSC) has proposed to
turn Singapore into a knowledge economy base, a global services
hub, a partner of multinational companies (MNC) and to train a
skillful workforce.
</P>
<P>
These highlights are included in a report prepared by the CSC
which will release it next month, he said.
</P>
<P>
Goh Chok Tong said that the CSC has identified the development
of the knowledge economy as a significant global trend which
Singapore should seriously prepare itself for, adding
"notwithstanding the current economic crisis, economic
liberalization and rapid technological improvements will continue
to reshape trade and investment flows, production patterns and
financial markets."
</P>
<P>
"The new knowledge economy is to the advantage of a
resource-poor country like Singapore," he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said the Singapore economy in the next
millennium will continue to be powered by the twin engines of
manufacturing and services.
</P>
<P>
"Manufacturing will continue to be an integral core of our
economy, " he said, adding "Complementing the manufacturing
sector, we will also build up into a global services hub."
</P>
<P>
He said Singapore will build up capabilities of research and
development, design, logistics, marketing and sales in addition to
production and develop new hub services in the area of healthcare,
education, media, communications and information technology
services."
</P>
<P>
Goh Chok Tong said Singapore recognizes the significant role
played by foreign multinational companies in the development of
the country's economy and holds MNCs will play their pivotal role
in Singapore's future economic development.
</P>
<P>
He also said his country will strengthen the base of local
enterprises to build them up as strategic partners to the MNCs.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister bills the quality of his country's workforce
as the key to continuing success.
</P>
<P>
"We will equip our workforce with suitable knowledge, skills
and enterprise," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
