<HEADLINE> Lao's National Assembly Session Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The second ordinary session of
the fourth National Assembly of Laos closed last weekend, Lao
official news agency KPL monitored here reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The session, opened on 29 September, has endorsed the law on
agriculture, and the amended law on the National Assembly, said
KPL.
</P>
<P>
During the ten-day session National Assembly members studied
and endorsed some important issues, including the government
report on the implementation of the socio-economic development and
the state budget for the 1997-1998. The session also unanimously
endorsed the 1998-1999 state budget.
</P>
<P>
The government reports on foreign affairs of Laos for the
1997-1998, and the line and tasks of foreign affairs for the
following year were presented to the session.
</P>
<P>
KPL said the Lao government will continue the country's
constant foreign policy for peace, national independence, and
international cooperation, international stability building,
creating the international atmosphere favorable for the national
construction and soliciting aid from friendly countries and
international organizations for socio-economic development.
</P>
</TEXT>
