<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's National Assembly to Convene Fourth Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The fourth session of Vietnam's
10th National Assembly (NA) will be convened here on October 28,
it was announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to an NA standing committee communique, the time for
the session was decided during a two-day meeting of NA standing
committee ended here last weekend.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the participants were reported on and gave
recommendations to the draft revised land law and draft revised
education law, which will be submitted to the NA year-end session.
</P>
<P>
The NA standing committee discussed and passed a resolution on
the promulgation of import tariffs which are categorized into
groups of items in line with tax rates and tax tables.
</P>
<P>
The communique points to the need to promulgate the new import
tariffs, which will replace the 1992 currently effective import
tariffs.
</P>
<P>
The promulgation of the new import tariffs is to re-arrange the
structure of the economy, increase and further expand foreign
trade activities, and protect domestic production.
</P>
<P>
It described the introduction of the new import tariffs as an
appropriate move of Vietnam to integrate itself into regional and
international trade organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
