<HEADLINE> ISF World Gymnasiad Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 13(Xinhua)-- The '98 international
Schoolsports Federation (ISF)World Gymnasiad lift its curtain
here on Tuesday night with 773 athletes from over 30 countries
and regions participating.
</P>
<P>
Lu Fuyuan, vice minister of Ministry of Education of China,
declared the opening of the Gymnasiad.
</P>
<P>
The ISF general secretary Defever Raymond said: "The future of
the society lies in the youth. Let's join together to give you
the best education. Let's be partners in organizing and offering
sports events for that. Let us build a peaceful and better world."
</P>
<P>
Raymond said that the world students games will serve as a
bridge for peace and understanding for the next century.
</P>
<P>
"Please catch the spirit of ISF, compete and meet each other,
some will win and I hope, and I'm even sure all will enjoy."
</P>
<P>
Students then performed in numbers entitled Sparks of Youth,
Rhythm of Motion and Bridge of Friendship.
</P>
<P>
Under the ISF regulations. participants must be students born
after 1981.
</P>
<P>
The Gymnasiad, a sports meet for the high school students, is
the last major gathering of this century and the first of its
kind held outside Europe.
</P>
<P>
The week-long event will offer 78 gold medals from track and
fields, swimming, gymnastics and rhythmic gymnastics.
</P>
<P>
The games are the biggest international sports meet hosted in
Shanghai after it staged the First East Asian Games in 1993 and
the Eighth National Games in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the opening ceremony are He Zhenliang, the
representative of International Olympic Committee president Juan
Antonio Samaranch and honorary president of Chinese Olympic
Committe, ISF president Boujon Jean Louis and Zhou Muyao , vice
mayor of Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
