<HEADLINE> Russian Soccer Chief Threatens To Step Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 13 (Xinhua)-- Russian football chief
Vyacheslav Koloskov said he would quit if representives at
Russian Football Union (RFU) conference next month force a vote
on his leadership.
</P>
<P>
Koloskov said the issue had not been on the official agenda of
the November 12 meeting, convened to resolve a number of pressing
issues including the funding of the national soccer teams.
</P>
