Professional Football League (PFL), the body that runs club
football, which warned Monday it would shut down Russian football
unless Koloskov's future was discussed.
</P>
<P>
Koloskov has showed his dissatisfaction with the government
for the sport's funding crisis, saying the authorities had not
stumped up the cash promised to develop the national game.
</P>
<P>
The head of Russian football expressed surprise at the PFL
call for his head, saying it had no right to issue ultimatums to
the RFU executive council, the body that sets the conference
agenda. 
