<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Group Ends Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The fifth session of the
Political and Administrative Group under the Preparatory Committee
of the Macao Special Administrative Region (MSAR) ended today
after a two-day session.
</P>
<P>
Participants engaged in heated discussions regarding drafts of
two documents, provisions for the formation of the government
nominating committee for the first MSAR government and the code
for committee members.
</P>
<P>
Professor Xiao Weiyun, who is responsible for contacting
members of the group living in China's inland areas, told Xinhua
News Agency that formation of the government nominating committee
is extremely important for ensuring the appointment of a highly
competent chief executive for administrative regions and the
effectiveness of the first MSAR government.
</P>
<P>
A National People's Congress (NPC) decision in 1993 requires
that members of the government nominating committee must represent
people from all walks of life, said Xiao, adding that the groups
completed a fact-finding tour of Macao in September.
</P>
<P>
The two drafts, which are based on the Basic Law of the Macao
Special Administrative Region and the NPC decision, will be
submitted to the fourth plenary session of the preparatory
committee scheduled for Zhuhai in early November, according to
Xiao.  
</P>
