<HEADLINE> Shanghai Bank Set to Grant Automobile Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) and the Shanghai
Automotive Industry (Group) Corporation signed an agreement
today on granting automobile loans.
</P>
<P>
Individuals, legal representative and various other economic
entities will be qualified for loans, according to Branch
president Jiang Jianqing.
</P>
<P>
Loans, which will carry terms ranging between three to five
years, will be limited to 80 percent of the total cost for a
vehicle, according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Local buyers purchasing Santana sedans manufactured by the
Shanghai-based automobile manufacturer, one of the three largest
venture of its kind in the country, will also qualify for loans.
</P>
<P>
The number of private vehicles in Shanghai, China's major
financial and commercial center stands at 8,000, compared with
some 400,000 units in Beijing, the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Local economists note the the new loan program is expected to
stimulate the city's private automobile market.  
</P>
