<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tomb Ground Nibbles S.Korean Usable Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 13 (Xinhua) -- South Korea has had some 19.98
million tombs, covering roughly 96,000 hectares as of October 1
this year, according to the Health and Welfare Ministry Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a report to the National Assembly, or parliament, the
ministry said that an additional 88 hectares will be turned into
burial ground every single year as some 200,000 dead people will
be interred.
</P>
<P>
Korean people traditionally prefer tomb burial to
cremation. Those who have their deceased parents cremated have been
traditionally viewed as totally unfilial children.
</P>
<P>
Under official statistics, the cremation rate stood at 20 percent
nationwide last year, which the government said is much
lower than the national average of 98 percent in the Netherlands,
97 percent in Japan and 69 percent in Britain.
</P>
<P>
The government has been encouraging its people to prefer
cremation as tomb burial will continue taking up huge land.
</P>
<P>
Now, South Korea has a population of some 44 million, with an
area of 99,447 square kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
