<HEADLINE> Drug Agency to Test Athletes in Pre-2000 Events </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- All athletes traveling to
Australia for pre Olympic warm-up event will face drug testing by
the Australian Sports Drug Agency (ASDA) , it announced in
Adelaide on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ASDA is facing a potential showdown with international
sports' federations as well as international Olympic Committee as
ASDA chairman Peter Baume on Tuesday also called on the IOC to
"stand back" and help create an independent international drug
testing authority.
</P>
<P>
"We are bound by legislation and that legislation will apply
in the lead up to the Sydney Olympics," he told a science and
medicine in sport conference in Adelaide on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Baume said there had already been embarrassment when
approaches were made to test visitors.
</P>
<P>
"We've had great difficulties already, but we have no option
but to enforce the law as it stands," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We have no degrees of freedom. They are aware that Australia
represents quite a level playing field, we do not want elite
athletes using drugs.
</P>
<P>
"He or she will be subject to the same rules of testing as
Australian athletes." 
</P>
