<HEADLINE> Balkan Leaders Calls for Peaceful Settlement of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANTALYA, TURKEY, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Balkan leaders
Tuesday called for a peaceful settlement of the Kosovo issue
within the framework of the U.N. Security Council Resolution
1199.
</P>
<P>
A joint declaration issued at the end of the two-day summit in
the southern Turkish port city of Antalya said that the Kosovo
crisis might spread to neighboring countries if it cannot be
solved as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"We reaffirmed our support to the U.N. Security Council
Resolutions 1160 and 1199 and we called on all parties for their
implementation in full in order to avoid further aggravation of
the crisis," the declaration said.
</P>
<P>
It stressed that the Kosovo issue should be politically solved
within the framework of ensuring sovereignty and territorial
integrity of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
"We emphasized the need for creating all necessary conditions
in Kosovo for the refugees and displaced persons to return freely
and safely to their homes," the statement added.
</P>
<P>
It said that "a breakthrough" achieved in the talks between
the representatives of the international community and the
Yugoslav government makes a peaceful settlement of the Kosovo
issue possible.
</P>
<P>
"We express our deep satisfaction of this new development
and of the understanding reached. We strongly support its full
implementation so as to bring lasting peace and stability in the
region," it added.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a joint press conference after the signing of the
joint declaration, Yugoslav Prime Minister Momir Bulatovic voiced
Belgrade's strong opposition to the NATO threat of air strikes
against the Yugoslav targets.
</P>
<P>
Bulatovic, who headed the Yugolsav delegation to the summit,
said that a possible NATO air attack might break the military
balance in the Balkan region and lead to arms races.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav delegation seems to be satisfied with the joint
document which did not use strong words condemning the Yugoslav
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
