<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Tang Guoqiang said today that the international
community should abide by the norms of international laws and the
general purpose and principles of the United Nations Charter, and
make unswerving efforts towards this end.
</P>
<P>
Responding to a question on the situation in Kosovo at a
routine press conference, Tang expressed deep concern about the
situation there. Tang said China has always stood against the use
of force and the threat to use force in international relations,
and the international community should seek truth from facts
before making an overall judgement on the Kosovo situation.
</P>
<P>
It should be noticed that large-scale military conflicts in
Kosovo have come to an end, the general situation is moving
towards a mitigation, and the concerned parties have staged new
proposals for a resolution through political negotiations, said
Tang, adding that "related talks can be resumed at an early
date."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out the Chinese side holds that, under the
pre-condition that the sovereignty and territorial integrity of
Yugoslavia are respected and the rights and interests of all
ethnic groups are ensured, to seek a peaceful resolution through
dialogs is the only way to fundamentally solve the Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
He added that Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan has sent
messages to the UN Secretary-General and foreign ministers of the
UN Security Council member states of the United States, Russia,
Britain and France, and met with the Yugoslavian Ambassador to
China, making clear China's stern position on the settlement of
the issue and appealing for effective measures taken by them for a
political settlement, so as to avoid using force.  
</P>
</TEXT>
