<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Confers with Angolan Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister
General Chi Haotian held talks here today with visiting Angolan
Defense Minister General Pedro Sebastiao who accompanied the
Angolan president on his visit to China.
</P>
<P>
As Africa is a major force of developing countries, Chi said,
China attaches great importance to the traditional friendship with
the African nations, and always supports the just struggles to
safeguarding their independence, sovereignty and dignity.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of Chinese Central Militart Commission
and state councillor, said that the Chinese army highly treasures
its friendship with the Angolan army and is ready to make efforts
to accelerate the development of state-to-state and army-to-army
relationship.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the friendly and cooperative
relations between the two armies will advance steadily at
multi-levels and in multi-fields and all directions.
</P>
<P>
Chi also briefed the guests on China's defensive national
defense policy and situation in army-building.
</P>
<P>
General Sebastiao cited China as an important force in
safeguarding world peace and stability, and expressed the
expectation that China could play a still more important role in
all aspects in the world.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he expressed his hope to learn during the current
visit China's experience in running the country and the army, and
to seek new channels to enhance friendly relations between the two
armies.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of general
staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, took part in the
talks. 
