<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Drops 7.6 Percent in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The value of re-exports of
Hong Kong decreased by 7.6 percent over a year earlier to 101.6
billion HK dollars (13.0 billion U.S. dollars) in August,
according to statistics released here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The value of domestic exports of Hong Kong decreased by 10.3
percent to 17.5 billion HK dollars (2.2 billion U.S. dollars) and
that of imports decreased by 14.2 percent to 119.9 billion HK
dollars (15.4 billion U.S. dollars) in August, the figures
released by the Census and Statistics Department revealed.
</P>
<P>
Comparing August 1998 with August 1997, decreases were recorded
in the value of re-exports to Singapore (-18.8 percent), Japan
(-18.6 percent), Taiwan (-12.3 percent), Germany (-11.2 percent),
China's mainland (-9.2 percent), the Netherlands (-7.7 percent)
and Canada (-3.4 percent).
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, increases were recorded in the value of
re-exports to the United Kingdom (+6.0 percent), France (+2.7
percent) and the United States (+1.4 percent).
</P>
<P>
Taking all destinations together, the value of re-exports in
the first eight months of 1998, at 768.5 billion HK dollars (98.5
billion U.S. dollars), was 4.1 percent lower than that in the same
period in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
