<HEADLINE> Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia to Begin China Trip Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- His Royal Highness Crown Prince
Abdullah Ibn abdul Aziz Al Saud, deputy prime minister and head of
the National Guard of Saudi Arabia, will pay an official visit to
China as of Wednesday, at the invitation of Chinese Premier Zhu
Rongji.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit to China by Abdullah Ibn abdul Aziz Al
Saud.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Zhu and Abdullah Ibn abdul Aziz Al Saud will
confer on bilateral relations and other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Beijing, the crown prince will travel to Xi'an
and Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
