<HEADLINE> Four Seats Still Open in Australia's Federal Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Howard government has won
78 seats in the 144 lower house seats where the result has been
announced, suggesting the coalition enjoys a 12-seat majority
after the October 3 election.
</P>
<P>
According to the Australian Election Commission (AEC), the
opposition, Australian Labor Party, won 65 in the total 148 seats
of the House of Representatives, with only one occupied by the
independent.
</P>
<P>
Four seats remain to be decided by just a few dozen votes, but
the AEC must wait until Friday for any remaining postal votes
before declaring the result in close seats.
</P>
<P>
Australian Democrats candidate John Schumann has conceded
defeat in Mayo in South Australia, where Foreign Minister
Alexander Downer has 51.66 percent of the two-party preferred
vote.
</P>
<P>
Of the four seats still open, Labor leads by a few votes in
Bass in Tasmania and Dickson in Brisbane and is favored to pick up
Kalgoorlie on preferences from independent Graeme Campbell, while
the Liberals lead in Townsville-based Herbert. 
</P>
</TEXT>
