<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Calls for Peaceful Solution of Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANTALYA, TURKEY, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav Prime
Minister Momir Bulatovic said Tuesday that the current Kosovo
issue should be solved through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference after the signing of a joint
declaration of the Balkan summit held here, Bulatovic said that
Yugoslavia is ready to have dialogs with major international
organizations to find a solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Large numbers of ethenic Albanians who fled the armed
conflicts in the Kosovo region have returned home, Bulatovic
said.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav prime minister also expressed satisfaction with
the outcome of the summit which ended Tuesday, calling it "a
success."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Albanian Foreign Minister Paskal Milo said that
Albania firmly supports the NATO decision to use all possible
means, including military action, to stop the bloody conflicts as
soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Milo said that the Yugoslav authorities should be held
responsible for the killings of many innocent ethnic Albanians
living in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Prime ministers from Greece, Romania, Bulgaria, Yugoslavia,
Macedonia, Turkey and the Albanian foreign minister discussed the
tensions in Kosovo during the two-day summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
