<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Science Ministers Meeting Ends in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The 8th meeting of the ASEAN
ministers for science and technology concluded here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, the ASEAN (Association of Southeast
Asian Nations) ministers for science and technology discussed
regional cooperation in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
A joint press release said the ministers recognized the new
challenges being faced by the science and technology sector as the
new millennium approaches.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the economic globalization, the rise of the
knowledge-based economy and the present economic slowdown in Asia
have implications on the direction and priorities of science and
technology development in ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The ministers called for urgent and coordinated action in the
science and technology sector to respond to the effects of these
developments in the economic arena.
</P>
<P>
The urged a review of past modalities of science and technology
cooperation in ASEAN and agreed to adopt in principle the
recommendations and guiding methodology proposed by the ASEAN
Committee on Science and Technology to develop innovative systems
for program management and revenue generation and to establish and
operate autonomous enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The ministers reiterated their call, made at their 7th meeting
in 1995 in Bangkok, Thailand, of the need to involve the private
sector and mobilize its resources for regional cooperative
projects in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
As a first step, the ministers agreed to augment the ASEAN
Science Fund, setting a target of 1 million U.S. dollars of
contribution from each member country, to be paid over a 10-year
period commencing next year.
</P>
<P>
The ministers agreed on the need for them to meet regularly
every three years, with an informal meeting in between. Malaysia
will host the first informal meeting of the science and technology
ministers.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that the 9th meeting of the ASEAN ministers
for science and technology will be held in Brunei in 2001.
</P>
<P>
The 8th meeting of the ASEAN ministers for science and
technology is part of the ASEAN Science and Technology Week being
held in Hanoi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
