<HEADLINE> APEC Trade Fair to Be Held in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The third APEC (Asia
Pacific Economic Cooperation) International Trade Fair will be
held in Malaysia in mid-November with most APEC member economies
confirming their participation.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair in Kuala Lumpur from November 13 to 16 with a
theme of "enhancing global competitiveness through technology and
human resource development" will focus on new technologies and
skilled manpower that contribute to the development of APEC
economies, Malaysian External Trade Development Corporation
(MATRADE) Chief Executive Mohammed Abdul Halim Abdul Rahman told a
press conference here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed said it will also feature products, technologies and
programs related to "emergency preparedness" as APEC strives to
build expertise in this area to handle environmental crisis in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Among the products and services which will be promoted include
high-tech computer parts and components, electrical appliances,
telecommunications equipment, food products, furniture, banking,
automotive parts and engineering consultancy.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed said that to date, besides more than 60 companies from
host Malaysia confirming their participation, 9 APEC economies --
Canada, Chile, Mexico, New Zealand, the Philippines, Singapore,
Chinese Taipei, Thailand, the United States, and two APEC member-
designates -- Peru and Russia have also confirmed their
presentation.
</P>
<P>
"We are happy to note that all member economies will
participate in this year's APEC trade fair despite the current
economic crisis experienced in some economies," Mohammed said.
</P>
<P>
He said the confirmed participation of these economies
certainly reflected their confidence in the economy of the region
and of the enormous opportunities that lie ahead.
</P>
<P>
He said that with 20,000 visitors including trade buyers from
overseas expected to attend the fair to be officiated by Malaysian
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad on November 13, the fair will be
an excellent venue for APEC economies to promote their products,
services and technologies.
</P>
<P>
MATRADE, the host organization for the fair, will
simultaneously organize the APEC Business Forum from November 13
to 16 here. 
</P>
