(NPC), expressed today the conviction that the current visit to
China by Angolan President Jose Etuardo Dos Santos will help
promote mutual understanding and trust as well as cooperative and
friendly relations between Angola and China.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Dos Santos here today, Li said that
Sino-Angolan friendly cooperation in all fields has been
increasing since the establishment of diplomatic relations,
especially since Dos Santos' last China tour in 1988.
</P>
<P>
China values the traditional friendship between the two
countries and is ready to further develop a long-term, stable and
cooperative relationship with Angola, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Dos Santos spoke highly of the achievements China has made in
economic construction and in maintaining political stability,
adding that China is playing an increasingly important and
constructive role in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan president told Li that he is satisfied with the
result of his current China visit and has been convinced that the
friendly and cooperative relations between China and Angola will
be further enhanced.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed Dos Santos and his entourage on the organization and
function of the NPC and the progress of China's socialist
democracy and legal system, saying that the NPC and the Angolan
National Assembly have witnessed good relations, and that exchange
and cooperation between the two parliaments constitutes an
important part of the two countries' ties.
</P>
<P>
Li said that he is willing to further boost exchanges between
the two parliaments to contribute to the growth of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Dos Santos briefed Li on the work of the Angolan National
Parliament and expressed his hope that cooperation between the two
parliaments will be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the peace process in Angola, Li said that China
has always supported the peace process, and appreciates the
efforts of the Angolan government to realize peace and national
reconciliation in the country.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of the NPC Standing Committee Cheng Siwei was also
present at the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
