<HEADLINE> 12 Die in Road Accident in S. Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people have died on the
spot when the truck they were traveling in overturned in Southern
Province, Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred Sunday morning near Choma, about 300
kilometers south of Lusaka, when the driver failed to negotiate a
corner. The truck hit into a hill and overturned, Zambia Daily
Mail reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Beenwell Chimfwembe has confirmed the
accident and said eight bodies of the twelve had not yet been
identified. 
