- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- About 21,000 Palestinian workers are allowed to
enter Israel from Tuesday since the Israeli army has lifted a
10-day closure on Gaza and the West Bank and a curfew on the West
Bank town of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
The closure was eased early Tuesday morning, several hours
after the nine-day Jewish holiday of Sukkot, a holiday to
celebrate harvest and commemorate the days the God led Israelis
out of Egypt in ancient times, ended. The Israeli army sealed off
Gaza and the West Bank last month following the threats by Islamic
militant group Hamas to attack Israel in retaliation of the
killing of two group members by Israeli soldiers.
(Israel-Closure-Lifting)
</P>
<P>
