</P>
<P>
ROME -- About 50.5 percent of Italians want a new government
and 44.4 percent favor early general elections, an opinion poll
showed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a poll by the SWG polling institute, 70.5 percent of
respondents believe the government crisis that burst onto the
political scene last Friday is bad for the country. The results,
to be published by the Catholic weekly Famiglia Cristiana, showed
that 57.6 percent of respondents said the outgoing Premier Romano
Prodi was "little or in no way effective" in government, yet he
was believed to be the most likely candidate to lead a new
government. (Italy-Government-Poll)
</P>
<P>
