<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Airport Reports Rise in Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Despite a slowdown in domestic
air traffic, the airport in the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone
witnessed sharp increases in both passengers and cargo transport in
the first nine months this year.
</P>
<P>
The airport handled 3.88 million passengers and 81,300 tons of
cargo and mail in the first nine months, up 18 percent and 12
percent respectively over the same period last year. A total of
40,231 aircraft took off and landed during the period.
</P>
<P>
The airport was renamed the Shenzhen Huangtian International
Airport last year, and the company running it is listed on the
Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Airport authorities attribute the airport's good performance
in part to a boost in international cargo business.
</P>
<P>
In April, the airport and an American company each injected
500,000 U.S. dollars to open the airport's international cargo
business.
</P>
<P>
In addition, regular air-cargo routes linking Shenzhen with
Kuala Lumpur and Seoul were opened in May and August.
</P>
<P>
A dozen air companies from the neighboring Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region have either opened or will open
international cargo transport stations in Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
A Canadian airline also plans to open an international cargo
air route with Shenzhen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
