<TEXT>
<P>
ELISTA, RUSSIA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- China and Russia
claimed the women's and men's team titles respectively as the
33rd Chess Olympiad concluded here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women tallied 29 points to secure their first ever
gold in Chess Olympiad, with Russia taking the silver and Georgia
the bronze.
</P>
