<DOCNO> XIE19981013.0168 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Background: Wang-Koo Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Koo Chen-fu, chairman of the
Taiwan-based Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF), is scheduled to
visit Shanghai and Beijing from October 14 to 19.
</P>
<P>
Koo will meet with Wang Daohan, president of the Chinese
mainland-based Association for Relations Across Taiwan Straits
(ARATS) during the visit.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first meeting between leaders of the two
authorized non-governmental organizations in five years.
</P>
<P>
Wang Daohan and Koo Chen-fu have already met at what is known
as the "Wang-Koo meeting" in Singapore from April 27 to 28,
1993. During that meeting, the two sides discussed cross-straits
economic exchanges and cooperation, exchanges of mail service,
trade, air and shipping services, as well as cross-straits
cooperation in the fields of labor, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The meeting resulted in several agreements -- "Agreement on
Institutionalized Contacts and Talks between the Two
Organizations," "Agreement on the Use and Verification of Notary
Certificates Across the Straits," and "Agreement on Inquires and
Compensation Concerning Registered Mail Across the Straits."
</P>
<P>
The two sides also reached a consensus that cross-straits
economic exchanges should be strengthened, and decided that
discussions be continued on the rights and interests of Taiwanese
investors in the Chinese mainland, and exchanges between
industrial circles of the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The "Wang-Koo meeting" was the highest-level non-governmental
meeting between the two sides since 1949.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), commented that the "Wang-Koo
meeting" was successful and marked an important and historic step
forward in the development of relations across the Straits.
</P>
<P>
The ARATS has extended great efforts to promote the forthcoming
meeting between Wang Daohan and Koo Chen-fu, and reached agreement
with the SEF that Wang and Koo will hold "free and easy talks on
issues of common concern and of respective concern" during their
meeting.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that President Jiang Zemin will meet with Mr. Koo
Chen-fu in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, and Chen Yunlin, director of the
Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council, will also meet with
Koo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
