<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing's Processing Trade Hits New Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's processing industry
continued to increase in the first eight months this year,
reaching a record 1.325 billion U.S. dollars, despite the effects
of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The volume accounted for 33 percent of Beijing's total exports
in the same period, and of the total trade volume, exports in the
January-August period was 950 million U.S. dollars, up 16.3 percent
over the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
Insiders surmise that increases in the processing industry can
be attributed to the adjustment of product mix, expanding use of
domestic raw materials, and electro-mechanical products and
high-tech products becoming a focal point in the growth of the
industry.
</P>
<P>
According to Beijing Customs, exports of electro-mechanical
products for the first eight months stood at 508 million U.S.
dollars, an increase of 52.8 percent over the same period last year,
and the exports of high-tech products increased by 141.6 percent,
reaching 214 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Related statistics also show that products of foreign-funded
enterprises constituted a major part of the local processing
industry, with their combined exports in the first eight months
reaching 685 million U.S. dollars, up 24.8 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
