<HEADLINE> Israel Lifts Closure on Gaza, West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 13 (Xinhua) -- About 21,000 Palestinian
workers are allowed to enter Israel from Tuesday since the Israeli
army has lifted a 10-day closure on Gaza and the West Bank and a
curfew on the West Bank town of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
The closure was eased early Tuesday morning, several hours
after the nine-day Jewish holiday of Sukkot, a holiday to
celebrate harvest and commemorate the days the God led Israelis
out of Egypt in ancient times, ended.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli army sealed off Gaza and the West Bank last month
following the threats by Islamic militant group Hamas to attack
Israel in retaliation of the killing of two group members by
Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The closure was eased briefly for several times but re-imposed
before the Sukkot.
</P>
<P>
The curfew on the Israel-controlled part of Hebron was imposed
on September 30 when more than a dozen Israeli soldiers patrolling
outside the Jewish settlements were injured in a grenade
attack. Clashes between the Palestinians and Israeli soldiers
occurred almost daily since then.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian officials have said that the closure on the West
Bank and Gaza has caused millions-of-dollars loss every day to the
Palestinian economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
