<HEADLINE> Urban Infrastructure Construction Focus in Henan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan
Province has drawn up a list of key infrastructure construction
projects in local urban areas for the next five years.
</P>
<P>
The province will focus on water supply projects in major
cities like Zhengzhou, Kaifeng, Luoyang and Pingdingshan,
adding 1.94 million tons to their daily water supply capacity.
</P>
<P>
More efforts will be made to complete the coal-gasification
project in Yima and speed up road construction in a bid to improve
urban transportation and ease traffic jams.
</P>
<P>
Henan will also further step up the transformation of power
grids in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
During the 1996-2000 period, the province intends to build an
additional sewage treatment capacity of 1.12 million tons per day
so that 35 percent of the province's waste water can be treated
before discharge.
</P>
<P>
This project will contribute to the national program designed
to clean up the Huaihe River, which flows through the province, by
the year 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
