<HEADLINE> Strong Typhoon Approaching Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 13 (Xinhua) -- A strong typhoon is approaching
the northern Philippines Tuesday with rains, forcing the
government to appeal to residents in coastal and low-lying areas
to evacuate to higher and safer grounds.
</P>
<P>
Secretary Orlando Mercado of the National Disaster Coordinating
Council said the disasters caused by past typhoons should be a
wake-up call for these people.
</P>
<P>
"These typhoons can cause us great damage, and people in the
vulnerable areas may be drowned," said Mercado, who also chairs
the Department of Defense.
</P>
<P>
While some people in flood-prone areas do not want to evacuate
to safer grounds, Mercado reiterated that the government appeal is
for their own good.
</P>
<P>
"We are appealing to you, for your own sake, to leave your
homes before you face danger," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to weather man, Typhoon Zeb (local name Iliang) would
cross the northern Philippines Wednesday. Zeb probably will
develop into a super typhoon and trigger another wave of
destruction in the country.
</P>
<P>
Typhoon is not a rare phenomenon in the northern Philippines.
Due to poor drainage system, every past typhoon brought floods and
economic damage to the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
