<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Angolan President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The visit to China by the
president of Angola will turn a new page in the friendship and
cooperative relations between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji made these remarks in a meeting with
Angolan President Jose Eduardo Dos Santos here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said friendship between the Chinese and Angolan peoples
extends far despite the distance between them.
</P>
<P>
Since China and Angola established diplomatic relations, the
two countries have witnessed stable bilateral ties and deepened
friendship between their peoples. They have extended cooperation
to many areas and have had friendly discussions and close
cooperation in international affairs, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Chinese government is willing to promote
bilateral friendship and cooperation with Angola for long-term and
stable development.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said Angola, with abundant natural resources, holds great
potential.
</P>
<P>
China supports the efforts of the Angolan government to develop
its economy, and is sincerely ready to assist Angola, he stressed,
adding that China wants to discuss with Angola ways to expand
bilateral economic ties in new areas and by new means.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government encourages businesses to seek
cooperation in Angola, and believes economic cooperation between
the two nations will grow continuously with common efforts.
</P>
<P>
Santos told Zhu he aims to promote bilateral ties by his
visit. He said his talks with Chinese President Jiang Zemin
yesterday was very fruitful and will be helpful for deepening and
expanding bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said Angola hopes to learn from China's experience in the
construction and development of rural areas, and wishes to enhance
cooperation with China in economic and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Zhu briefed the visitor on China's economic
situation, and Santos discussed the domestic situation and peace
process in Angola.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said peace and stability is a presupposition for economic
development. "No peaceful environment, no development," he
emphasized.
</P>
<P>
The premier said the Chinese government supports Angola's peace
process, and hopes Angola will soon realize peace and
reconciliation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
