<HEADLINE> India Airlifts 40 Tons of Wheat to Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 13 ( Xinhua) -- India airlifted 40 metric
tons of wheat Monday to Bangladesh as part of humanitarian aid for
flood victims in the neighboring country.
</P>
<P>
The wheat provided by the National Seeds Corporation were sent
to Dhaka, capital of the country, aboard a plane of the Indian Air
Force from Agra, 200 kilometers southeast of here, the National
Herald daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On request from the Bangladeshi government, India decided to
provide the country with nearly 600 tons of wheat. The remaining
aid will be sent via train to Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh has suffered heavily in one of the worst floods in
the last ten years. The floods, the longest in the country's
history, have killed at least 850 people, left 25 million homeless
or marooned and inflicted massive damage to agriculture, industry
and infrastructure since early July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
