<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Warns Against Colonialists' Interference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader
Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt has warned his people in the country
against the danger of interference by existing colonialists who
are trying to influence the nation through different ways.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the State Peace and Development
Council, made the remarks at a coordination meeting here Monday on
 holding the Exhibition '98 to Revitalize and Foster Patriotic
Spirit.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt was quoted by Tuesday's newspaper the New Light of
Myanmar as saying that the danger of interference of colonialists
still exists now, who are trying to gain influence through
economic, cultural, religious and social ways.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the entire nation and the race could become
a minion of neocolonialists again if colonialists could manipulate
present youths at will.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Exhibition '98 to Revitalize and Foster
Patriotic Spirit is to be held to show that there are firm
historical links that Myanmars have evolved through the Stone Age,
the Bronze Age, the Iron Age and different stages of civilization
in their own nation.
</P>
<P>
