enterprises from 60 countries gathered in the Brazilian city of
Sao Paulo on Monday for a three-day conference here.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the conference includes job creation, regional
development and credit concession, reports said.
(Brazil-Company-Conference)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- A number of commercial banks have cut their deposit
interest rates by as much as eight percentage points in the wake
of the rupiah's recent rally and falling inflation, the Jakarta
Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
These banks have been offering one-month deposit rates at below
60 percent per annum, much lower than the 64 percent maximum
deposit rate that the government is guaranteeing this week.
((Indonesia-Interest Rates)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles -- A leading U.S. direct marketer has acquired an
online business organization, creating the world's largest trade
association for business on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The 81-year-old Direct Marketing Association (DMA) announced
Monday the acquisition of the Association for Interactive Media
(AIM), founded in 1993, during the ongoing DMA 81st annual
conference in San Francisco. (US-Online Business-Acquisition)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian Oil Minister Hamdi el-Bambi denied on Monday
reports that Egypt planned to slash its oil output if members of
the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) decide to
reduce their production ceiling.
</P>
<P>
The 11-member cartel is due to consider during their meeting in
Vienna November 25 further lowering their production quotas in
another attempt to shore up oil prices and ease the world oil
glut. (Egypt-Oil-Output Cut)
</P>
<P>
