since Thailand took strides in reforming its ailing financial
sector following the financial crisis that erupted in July last
year. (Thailand-Bank Privatization)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan's House of Councillors, the upper house of
parliament, enacted Monday a set of banking reform bills designed
to fix the country's ailing banking sector.
</P>
<P>
The enactment ended months of political wrangling between the
ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) and opposition groups led by
the Democratic Party of Japan (DPJ) over how to handle Japanese
banks' massive bad loan problem. (Japan-Bank Reform-Bills)
