<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Set Up Disaster Management Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government is to
set up a Disaster Management Committee to handle both national and
local disasters, according to the Ministry of Social Services
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The committee will be assisted by disaster investigation
committees at divisional secretariats to obtain information during
natural disasters, ministry sources said.
</P>
<P>
A data bank will be set up by the committee to provide data for
planning short and long term solutions for damages caused by
natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
Under this program when a disaster occurs alternative
employment will be provided for victims of natural disasters
during the affected period, the sources added. 
