<HEADLINE> Moldova Supports Political Solution to Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Moldavian President Peter
Luchinsky said on Monday his country supported only political
solutions to the Kosovo crisis and opposed the use of force by the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
Luchinsky stressed at a meeting in Chisinau, capital of the
Moldavian Republic, that the Kosovo crisis could only be solved
through political means and any military actions would incur
serious consequences in the Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
No efforts should be spared in seeking a peaceful solution,
including taking more stringent action to bring the relevant
parties back to the negotiating table, he said, emphasizing
however that force should never be used.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time Luchinsky has made such a statement on
the crisis in the last week.
</P>
<P>
During a one-day informal visit to Romania last Saturday,
Luchinsky expressed his hope that diplomacy would bring an end to
the crisis. 
