Opening the conference, Brazilian Vice President Marco Maciel
said small and medium sized companies are playing an important
role in the world because of their adaptability to changes in the
global economy.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the conference includes job creation, regional
development and credit concession, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Key figures present at the opening ceremony included Brazilian
Industry Minister Jose Botafogo, General Director of Japan's
National Agency of Small and Medium Companies Makoto Kondo and
United Nations Economic Commissioner for Latin America and the
Caribbean Renato Baumann.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the 25th of its kind, was sponsored by Sao
Paulo's Commercial Association and the Brazilian Service of Small
and Medium Sized Companies Support. 
</P>
</TEXT>
