<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Exports Down 6.7 Percent in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- China's exports amounted to
15.48 billion U.S. dollars in September, a drop of 6.7 percent
from a year ago, according to Customs statistics just released.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said the Asian financial crisis is having a
deepening impact on China's exports.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China's imports amounted to 11.54 billion
U.S. dollars in September, up 0.6 percent, while total foreign
trade stood at 27.02 billion dollars, 3.7 percent lower than the
1997 figure.
</P>
<P>
China's exports in the first nine months this year amounted to
134.13 billion U.S. dollars, and imports totalled 98.82 billion,
increasing 3.9 percent and 0.4 percent respectively over the same
1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Although the nation's exports continued to grow this year,
the growth rate declined month by month, and slipped by a large
margin compared with last year's 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
Exports from July to September decreased 2.2 percent from last
year, while imports remained at last year's level.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
