<DOCNO> XIE19981013.0240 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5th ASEAN Science, Technology Week Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The 5th Science and Technology
Week of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) was
launched at a ceremony here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Present at the ceremony were Vietnam's Prime Minister Phan Van
Khai, and representatives of the embassies of the ASEAN countries
as well as some dialogue partners.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN is facing the financial-economic crisis which caused
serious difficulties in food security, natural disaster prevention
and environmental protection, the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the situation is requiring feasible and
effective scientific and technological approaches.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam will pool efforts to team up with the other ASEAN
countries to resolve the problems, Khai said.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam encourages the application of new scientific
achievements and technological solutions to industrialization and
modernization, especially in biology, information technology,
automation, environmental protection and personnel training.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister hoped that the meeting of ASEAN relevant
bodies would put forth appropriate ways to foster more regular and
tighter bonds of partnership between Vietnamese and ASEAN
scientists.
</P>
<P>
As many as 500 scientists of the ASEAN member countries and
their dialogue partners of Canada, Australia, India and the United
States presented over 400 scientific reports at scientific
seminars and exhibitions organized during the week.
</P>
<P>
The eighth meeting of ASEAN ministers for science and
technology is being held here Monday and Tuesday within the
framework of the ASEAN Science and Technology Week.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will review the implementation of programs and
projects that are being carried out by the ASEAN Committee on
Science and Technology and work out measures and orientations for
cooperation in the coming time.
</P>
<P>
The participants will discuss issues relating to science and
technology of the ASEAN countries within the Hanoi plan of action
with the aim to implement the ASEAN vision 2020 which will be
submitted to the sixth ASEAN summit scheduled to be convened in
Hanoi on December this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
