<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebels Abduct Youth As Conscripts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) are forcibly conscripting
youth in some villages in the east of the country, according to
reports reaching here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 15-year war against the government
for a separate state in the north and east of the country.
</P>
<P>
Frustrated due to the lack of manpower, the LTTE leadership has
issued orders to abduct those who cannot be persuaded to join the
LTTE, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE local leaders in Batticaloa are combing the area in
search of youth to be conscripted, said the reports, adding that
70 young men and women have been forcibly taken away from some
villages in the Batticaloa district recently. 
</P>
