<HEADLINE> Japan Grants Loans for Water Supply Project in Shanxi Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Overseas Economic
Cooperation Fund is to grant 160 million U.S. dollars in loans for
a water supply project in Taiyuan, capital of north China's Shanxi
Province, according to an agreement signed here recently.
</P>
<P>
The project is estimated to cost more than 2.3 billion yuan and
includes a water treatment plant with a daily capacity of 800,000
tons, more than 160 kilometers of pipelines and two relay pumping
stations.
</P>
<P>
The entire project is expected to be completed in the year
2003, with the first phase of construction work on the water
treatment plant scheduled to be finished in 2001, enabling the
plant to treat 400,000 tons of water per day.
</P>
<P>
This project is part of the overall plan to divert Yellow River
water into the province.  
</P>
