<HEADLINE> Henan Province Improving Telecom Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Business in the
telecommunications sector in central China's Henan Province has
grown by 50 percent for five consecutive years and is expected to
hit nine billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
This is a result of growing local investment in the sector, and
this year alone, more than 10 billion yuan of investment is
expected to be put in the industry.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the year, the province has added 670,000
lines to the handling capacity of digital mobile phones and
increased by 1.3 million lines the capacity of its switchboards.
</P>
<P>
This has paved the way for the installation of telephones in
all local villages by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
This year, the province also increased its long-distance
telephone lines to 25,000 and added 2,500 kilometers to its
long-distance optic-fiber lines.
</P>
<P>
Henan now attaches more importance to the introduction of
information technology in the telecommunications industry and
encourages the expansion of multi-media telecom network.  
</P>
