<HEADLINE> New Peruvian Foreign Minister Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Fernando de Trazegnies was sworn
in as Peru's new Foreign Minister on Monday, replacing Eduardo
Ferrero Costa.
</P>
<P>
Ferrero resigned suddenly on October 2, reportedly because he
had been ignored during the Peru-Ecuador peace talks, which were
conducted by Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori and his Ecuadoran
counterpart Jamil Mahuad.
</P>
<P>
Following the new minister's swearing-in ceremony, De
Trazegnies affirmed that Peru would not give "a single centimeter"
in its border dispute with Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
Peace talks seeking to settle the border conflict between Peru
and Ecuador have been bogged down because of differences over the
demarcation of a 78-kilometer area on their common border.
</P>
<P>
The new Peruvian foreign minister heads the Peruvian delegation
in the Ecuador-Peru Border Settlement Commission and is also one
of the main advisors for Fujimori in the peace negotiations that
started in 1995. 
</P>
