<HEADLINE> Barkley Says Jordan Is Done </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- NBA's star Charles Barkley
said Michael Jordan will retire from pro basketball and that he
may not be far behind.
</P>
<P>
Barkley was a guest of San Diego Padres owner John Moores
during Game 3 of the National League Championship Series. The
Padres beat the Atlanta Braves 4-1 to take a 3-0 lead in the
best-of-seven series.
</P>
<P>
It's the second weekend in a row Barkley has attended a Padres
playoff game. Barkley and Jordan are both free agents without
contracts, although the NBA's lockout has suspended all player
transactions.
</P>
<P>
"He's done," Barkley said about Jordan, the Bulls' star who
has won six NBA titles in the last eight seasons. "He's very
frustrated with the whole Bulls organization. I've talked with
him a lot about this and I just don't see him coming back."
</P>
<P>
Barkley, who played last season for the Rockets, said he
hasn't made a decision about his own status. "There are some
teams I can help. But there's no sense in coming back just to
play," he said. 
</P>
