<HEADLINE> Jarrett Wins Winston 500 Auto Racing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Dale Jarrett held off a
pack of challengers over the last 13 laps as he won both the
Winston 500 and a one million U.S. dollars bonus on a day when
Jeff Gordan ran second and took a big step toward wrapping up his
third Winston Cup auto championship in four years.
</P>
<P>
While an eight-car pack was exchanging positions behind him,
Jarrett kept his Ford Taurus out front, winning his third race of
the year and the 18th of his NASCAR career.
</P>
<P>
An 11-car crash on the 136th of 188 laps sent Ernie Irvan to a
Birmingham hospital. Irvan, who survived a near-fatal crash in
August 1994, was awake and talking when taken from his battered
car.
</P>
<P>
A CAT scan was negative and no broken bones were found, but
Irvan was being kept overnight at the hospital for observation.
