<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Reports Rise in Agriculture Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica's agriculture
exports in the first eight months of this year earned 1.086
billion U.S. dollars, 8.52 percent up from the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released on Monday by the Foreign Trade
Ministry, out of that total amount, 399.10 million dollars were
from banana exports, 290.04 million dollars from coffee sales, and
68.79 million dollars from pineapple exports.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period in 1997, pineapple exports in the
period increased by 15.97 percent and banana by 8.20 percent.
</P>
<P>
But coffee exports fell by 1.38 percent.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica is the world's second biggest banana producer and
exporter after Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
Currently it has more than 50,000 hectares dedicated to banana
cultivation. 
</P>
