<HEADLINE> Families Use Hot Springs in North China Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 120,000 people in
this port city now take showers with hot springs water at
home, according to a seminar on hot-springs engineering held
here recently.
</P>
<P>
The hot-springs users live in Tanggu, a coastal district in the
eastern section of Tianjin, and account for 25 percent of the
district's population. The development of terrestrial heat in the
district ranks second in the world, following Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Over the past ten years, the city has drilled 26 terrestrial
heat wells, providing a heating system for an area of 830,000 square
meters. The district has also set up a world-class digital and
automatic control system for the hot springs.  
