<HEADLINE> Commercial Housing Sells Well in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, one of the four
municipalities in China directly under the central government,
sold commercial housing with a total floor space of 1.84 million
square meters in the first eight months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 71 percent of the commercial flats were
bought by individual purchasers, 10 percent higher than the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
A municipal official attributed the enthusiastic purchase of
commercial housing to the implementation of housing reform which
began in 1994. Under the reform, the government ceased the
decades-long practice of distributing housing to urban residents,
and started encouraging individuals to purchase their own
residences.
</P>
<P>
In the first eight months this year, the city dismantled old
and dilapidated houses over an area of 1.68 million square meters,
and provided their former inhabitants with 3.4 billion yuan in
low-interest loans for buying new flats in other areas.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Tianjin encouraged local residents to
exchange old flats for new ones by lowering transaction taxes. In
the eight months to August, 2,492 households took advantage of
this opportunity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
