<HEADLINE> Academy of Sciences to Initiate Innovative Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS) plans to initiate 12 innovative projects this year to form a
group of new research centers, according to CAS officials.
</P>
<P>
CAS will establish the Shanghai Life Science Academy based on
relevant scientific institutes in China's major commercial and
financial center. The institutes will function as united
scientific organizations, with the academy providing
administration and development funds.
</P>
<P>
The National Astronomical Observation Center will be
established on the basis of the Beijing Astronomical Observatory,
and the Shaanxi Observatory will be redesignated as the National
Timing Center.
</P>
<P>
The projects will also include establishment of the Beijing
Academy of Material Sciences, Academy of Mathematics and eight
other research institutes and centers.
</P>
<P>
The innovative program will go far beyond scientific research
into the management system reform, according Guo Chuanjie, deputy
secretary of the CAS Committee of the Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
The projects will optimize the distribution of scientific
resources and improve the efficiency of research and development
amongst various CAS institutes, said Guo.
</P>
<P>
He added that a number of projects already commenced in June
this year and dozens will be carried out before the year 2005.
</P>
