<HEADLINE> Thailand to Open Shuttle Link for Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 13 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will launch a
special train service to shuttle between two sports complexes
during the December 6-20 Asian Games, officials of the State
Railway of Thailand (SRT) said here today.
</P>
<P>
The SRT will operate 14 air-conditioned trains a day between
newly-renovated Chiang Rak and Hua Mark railways running through
the city and its surroundings.
</P>
<P>
Chiang Rak is located north of Bangkok near the Thammasat
Sports Complex while Hua Mark lies east of Bangkok near sports fac
ilities in the Sports Authorities of Thailand compound in the Hua
Mark area.
</P>
<P>
The SRT will introduce special ticket for the train service.
Tickets priced at 50, 250 and 400 baht (one dollar equals 37
baht) will allow unlimited trips a day, a week, and for the whole
event respectively. 
</P>
