<DOCNO> XIE19981013.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Folding Toilets to Benefit Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 13 (Xinhua) -- A shipment of folding toilets
will travel a long way from the Chinese capital to central China's
Hunan Province and help flood victims there live healthier and
more conveniently.
</P>
<P>
He Enxiang invented this new toilet when he became aware that
flood victims in central China had no clean place to relieve
themselves.
</P>
<P>
He said the new toilet is light and easy to transport, one
person can install it in just ten minutes, and human waste is
collected in bags, leaving no pollution to the environment.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health hailed the new product and believes it
can be used as a disaster-relief item when serious natural
disasters occur.
</P>
<P>
Yin Dakui, vice-minister of health, spoke highly of the
invention and said it will benefit the collection of human waste
in disaster-hit areas and efficiently check the spread of
infectious diseases.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
