<HEADLINE> FA Confirms Hartson Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- English Premier club West Ham
striker John Hartson must appear before Football Association
disciplinary chiefs after kicking teammate Eyal Berkovic in the
face during a training ground incident.
</P>
<P>
An FA statement said on Monday: "He has been charged with
misconduct and he has 14 days to respond, as usual."
</P>
<P>
The Welsh international has already been fined 10,000 by his
club for the incident - the maximum allowed by the Professional
Footballers' Association.
</P>
<P>
Manager Harry Redknapp has ordered Hartson to pay two weeks
wages to the charity Leukaemia Busters.
</P>
<P>
"Despite Berkovic asking me not to fine Hartson, that is what
I have done," said Redknapp.
</P>
<P>
"John has apologised for the incident but he has still been
fined two weeks' wages - the maximum the PFA will allow us.
Hopefully that will be the end of the matter."
</P>
<P>
Berkovic has assured chief executive, Peter Storrie, that he
will be staying at the club despite the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
