<HEADLINE> Liatti, Makinen Share Lead in San Remo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Italian Piero Liatti and world
champion Tommi Makinen of Finland shared the lead in the San Remo
rally after five stages on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Subaru driver Liatti set the fastest time in the first and
fifth stages of his home event while Mitsubishi's Makinen was
dominant in the second, third and fourth.
</P>
<P>
The two were tied on 51 minutes 43 seconds.
</P>
<P>
World championship leader Carlos Sainz of Spain trailed 17.9
seconds to finish third. 
</P>
