<HEADLINE> China on Financing of Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The discussion on
financing of development should focus on the important question of
inter-governmental international cooperation, China stressed here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 53rd session of the General Assembly, Chinese
Deputy Permanent Representative to the United Nations Shen Guofang
said that for a long time, the vast number of developing countries
had not seen much improvement in the unfavorable external
environment surrounding them, and at the same time, the
accelerated pace of the economic globalization process had
confronted them with new challenges.
</P>
<P>
Shen said it went without saying that the economic and social
development of a country could only be achieved by mainly relying
on its own strength and resources, but at the forum of the United
Nations, discussions on financing of development should naturally
concentrate on actions that should be taken at the
inter-governmental level.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Shen said many developing countries were faced with
the problem of not being able to meet their development needs by
solely relying on the market or their own domestic efforts, and
under such circumstances, overemphasis on their domestic
responsibilities would not help them in their efforts to free
themselves from the current situation and to strengthen their
capacities for self-reliance.
</P>
<P>
Shen stressed that it was a responsibility incumbent upon
countries and governments concerned to reverse the downward spiral
of official development assistance, and to provided developing
countries with much-needed financial help. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981013.0307 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-12 19:11 </DATE_TIME>
