<HEADLINE> China on External Debt, Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Efforts had been made by
some international organizations and creditor countries in
alleviating the debt burdens of heavily indebted countries, China
stressed here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 53rd session of the General Assembly, Chinese
Deputy Permanent Representative to the United Nations Shen Guofang
added there was still a long distance to go before reacing the
goal of resolving the debt crisis once and for all.
</P>
<P>
The current financial crisis had worsened the debt problem for
some developing countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Shen said it was hoped that relevant international
organizations and creditor countries would take a more active
stance by moving to speed up the rather slow implementation of the
"heavily indebted poor countries" initiative.
</P>
<P>
Shen said bolder steps should be taken with regard to the
eligibility criteria and duration of implementation, and concrete
support should also be given to countries hit by recent financial
crisis, so that more developing countries would be relieved of the
debt burden and achieve stable economic and social development.
</P>
</TEXT>
