<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- An application from Zambia
Electricity Supply Corporation (ZESCO) to increase electricity
tariffs has been turned down, the country's Energy Regulation
Board (ERB) announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
ERB chairman Raphael Salesini said that following a public
hearing held early this month ERB resolved that the planned
tariff increase be rejected.
</P>
<P>
