objections raised by various consumers which culminated into the
public hearing plus the facts and figures available to ERB," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the tariffs will only be reviewed on an annual basis
starting in April next year, taking into consideration that ZESCO
should be able to earn a rate of return of at least six percent
by the financial year 2000-2001.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the state-run power company to take necessary
measures to reduce costs, particularly administrative costs, and
bad debts which should significantly be reduced to improve the
billing and collection systems.
</P>
<P>
ZESCO should be committed to and ensure that they increase the
number of customers by 20,000 a year, he said. 
