<HEADLINE> Six Killed on Rail Tracks in Southern U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Six people, who were
believed to have been sleeping on the rail tracks, were killed
when a freight train struck them early Monday in south Texas.
</P>
<P>
The 105-car train was on its way to Brownsville from Houston
when the accident occurred at 3:15 a.m. local time in Kenedy
County, about 100 kilometers north of Brownsville, an Associated
Press report said.
</P>
<P>
The crew saw the people lying between the tracks, but it was
too late to stop the train, which need at least 1.5 kilometers to
get a halt. The cars of the train were not derailed in the
accident.
</P>
<P>
No details about the victims were reported, but it mentioned
that some undocumented immigrants sleep between train tracks
believing it could protect them from snakes. 
</P>
