<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Back in Moscow After Shortened Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
returned to Moscow Monday evening at the end of a shortened trip
to Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin' plane landed at the local Vnukovo-2 airport at 23:56
local time (19:56 GMT), the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin was scheduled to end the visit to Kazakhstan Tuesday,
but his doctors insisted that he cut short the trip after he was
diagnosed of bronchitis.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Yeltsin is been treated with
anti-inflammatory medicines and antibiotics, but doctors haven't
told him to stay in bed.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's spokesman Dmitry Yakushkin, who is accompanying
Yeltsin on the Central Asia tour, told reporters that Yeltsin
caught a cold since the weekend, after a hard week of dealing with
urgent social and economic problems and serious international
issues.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin suffered two heart attacks in 1996 in the wake of the
June 16 presidential election. He also had quintuple heart bypass
surgery in November that year. 
</P>
