<HEADLINE> Ghana's Debt Payment Pattern Praised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Debt Relief International
(DRI), an international non-governmental organization, said
Monday that Ghana's debt payment pattern is one of the best in
the world, Ghana News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
It quoted DRI Director Mathew Martin as saying this when
reviewing the key issues of Ghana's future debt strategy at a
workshop in Ghanaian capital Accra. The DRI helps the
heavily-indebted poor countries (HIPC) to manage their debts.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is part of a series under the HIPC Debt Strategy
Capacity Building Program funded by the governments of Austria,
Switzerland, Sweden, Denmark and Britain.
</P>
<P>
Officials of Ghanaian Ministry of Finance put the country's
external debt ratio at 25 percent of national budget, said the
report.
</P>
<P>
Ghana's external debt stands at 5.6 billion U.S. Dollars and
is expected to rise in the medium term, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the performance of other countries, especially
developing ones, Matin said, "Ghana is rated as one of the best
in the world".
</P>
<P>
"Ghana has a good record of paying her debt on time. There
have not been any arrears in the last few years", Matin added.
</P>
<P>
Ghana's Deputy Finance Minister Victor Selormey said at the
workshop that good and effective debt management at the macro and
micro levels has to be coordinated in the context of a
well-thought-out borrowing strategy which will be in consonance
with monetary, fiscal and balance of payment policies among other
things.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister indicated that government's main concern
is debt sustainability since a large debt overhang still exists,
saying "the burden of external and domestic debt has increased."
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Ghana is learning from the Asia
financial crisis and also ensuring that debt from the private
sector, whether guaranteed or not, is given serious attention.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
