<HEADLINE> Dow up to above 8000 Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 12 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Stocks surged on Monday,
amid better corporate earnings reports for the third quarter and
encouragement from overseas markets, with the blue-chip
index up to the above 8000 level.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 101.95 to 8001.47,
turning back into positive territory for the year which started at
7908.25.
</P>
<P>
The Dow, which gained 167.61 on Friday, has bounced more than
500 points from the bottom of a 274 point fall on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Broad market indicators also extended the gains on Friday with
the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rising 13.32 to 997.71, and the
technology-heavy Nastaq composite index up 53.61 to 1546.10.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues led decliners 2139 to 992 with 375 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Transaction volume of 688.26 million shares at 4 p.m. on New
York Stock Exchange was down from 876.09 million shares on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 6.25 to 492.95, the American
Stock Exchange composite index rose 6.28 to 581.01 and the Russell
2000 index of smaller companies rose 7.22 to 325.62.
</P>
<P>
News reports about higher earnings in U.S. auto,
pharmaceuticals and other industries for the third quarter boosted
the market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
There are also reports about a new round of interest rate cuts
worldwide to help check the plunge in many bourses.
</P>
<P>
European and Japanese markets surged mostly on Monday, sending
positive signals to New York, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Despite the gain on Monday, the Dow is still more than 1300
points below the July 17 record of 9337.97. 
</P>
</TEXT>
